Before diving into the best practices, please note that you need to adapt the globs depending on your project's specific file structure and requirements.

---
name: sqlite-best-practices.mdc
description: Best practices for using SQLite database
globs: **/*.{ts,tsx,js,jsx,sql}
---

- Use parameterized queries to prevent SQL injection
- Implement proper transaction management
- Regularly backup your database
- Use indexes for frequently queried columns
- Avoid recreating the database on every run

---
name: cms-best-practices.mdc
description: Best practices for implementing a Content Management System
globs: **/*.{ts,tsx,js,jsx}
---

- Implement a clear separation between content and presentation
- Use a robust API for content management
- Implement user authentication and authorization
- Ensure content versioning and backup
- Optimize for content editor experience

---
name: ui-ux-best-practices.mdc
description: Best practices for modern UI/UX design
globs: **/*.{ts,tsx,js,jsx,css}
---

- Follow current design trends and patterns
- Ensure high usability and user-friendliness
- Implement responsive design across all devices
- Use consistent typography and color schemes
- Conduct user testing and iterate based on feedback

---
name: responsive-design-best-practices.mdc
description: Best practices for creating responsive designs
globs: **/*.{ts,tsx,js,jsx,css}
---

- Use flexible grid layouts
- Implement media queries for different screen sizes
- Optimize images for various resolutions
- Ensure touch-friendly interactions on mobile
- Test on multiple devices and browsers

---
name: csrf-protection-best-practices.mdc
description: Best practices for implementing CSRF protection
globs: **/*.{ts,tsx,js,jsx}
---

- Use CSRF tokens for all state-changing operations
- Implement token validation on the server-side
- Use secure, HttpOnly cookies for token storage
- Implement double-submit cookie pattern
- Regularly rotate CSRF tokens for added security

---
name: error-handling-best-practices.mdc
description: Best practices for error handling and prevention
globs: **/*.{ts,tsx,js,jsx}
---

- Implement comprehensive error logging
- Use try-catch blocks for critical operations
- Provide user-friendly error messages
- Implement proper error boundaries in React
- Regularly review and fix coding errors
